anagement for agents. Compression detection, auto-snapshots, and semantic search. Use when agents need to detect compression risk before memory loss, save context snapshots, search historical memories, or track memory usage patterns. Never lose context again.\n            - generic [ref=e833]:\n              - generic [ref=e834]: by\n              - generic [ref=e836]: \"@marmikcfc\"\n          - generic [ref=e837]:\n            - generic [ref=e838]:\n              - img [ref=e839]\n              - text: 9.3k\n            - generic [ref=e843]: ★ 41\n            - generic [ref=e844]: 1 v\n        - link \"Memory Hygiene /memory-hygiene Audit, clean, and optimize Clawdbot's vector memory (LanceDB). Use when memory is bloated with junk, token usage is high from irrelevant auto-recalls, or setting up memory maintenance automation. by @dylanbaker24 7.9k ★ 6 1 v\" [ref=e845] [cursor=pointer]:\n          - /url: /dylanbaker24/memory-hygiene\n          - generic [ref=e846]:\n            - generic [ref=e847]:\n              - generic [ref=e848]: Memory Hygiene\n              - generic [ref=e849]: /memory-hygiene\n            - generic [ref=e850]: Audit, clean, and optimize Clawdbot's vector memory (LanceDB). Use when memory is bloated with junk, token usage is high from irrelevant auto-recalls, or setting up memory maintenance automation.\n            - generic [ref=e852]:\n              - generic [ref=e853]: by\n              - generic [ref=e855]: \"@dylanbaker24\"\n          - generic [ref=e856]:\n            - generic [ref=e857]:\n              - img [ref=e858]\n              - text: 7.9k\n            - generic [ref=e862]: ★ 6\n            - generic [ref=e863]: 1 v\n        - link \"Agent Memory /agent-memory Persistent memory for AI agents to store facts, learn from actions, recall information, and track entities across sessions. by @Dennis-Da-Menace 5.1k ★ 3 1 v\" [ref=e864] [cursor=pointer]:\n          - /url: /Dennis-Da-Menace/agent-memory\n          - generic [ref=e865]:\n            - generic [ref=e866]:\n              - generic [ref=e867]: Agent Memory\n              - generic [ref=e868]: /agent-memory\n            - generic [ref=e869]: Persistent memory for AI agents to store facts, learn from actions, recall information, and track entities across sessions.\n            - generic [ref=e871]:\n              - generic [ref=e872]: by\n              - generic [ref=e874]: \"@Dennis-Da-Menace\"\n          - generic [ref=e875]:\n            - generic [ref=e876]:\n              - img [ref=e877]\n              - text: 5.1k\n            - generic [ref=e881]: ★ 3\n            - generic [ref=e882]: 1 v\n        - link \"Memory System V2 /memory-system-v2 Fast semantic memory system with JSON indexing, auto-consolidation, and <20ms search. Capture learnings, decisions, insights, events. Use when you need persistent memory across sessions or want to recall prior work/decisions. by @kellyclaudeai 3.5k ★ 10 1 v\" [ref=e883] [cursor=pointer]:\n          - /url: /kellyclaudeai/memory-system-v2\n          - generic [ref=e884]:\n            - generic [ref=e885]:\n              - generic [ref=e886]: Memory System V2\n              - generic [ref=e887]: /memory-system-v2\n            - generic [ref=e888]: Fast semantic memory system with JSON indexing, auto-consolidation, and <20ms search. Capture learnings, decisions, insights, events. Use when you need persistent memory across sessions or want to recall prior work/decisions.\n            - generic [ref=e890]:\n              - generic [ref=e891]: by\n              - generic [ref=e893]: \"@kellyclaudeai\"\n          - generic [ref=e894]:\n            - generic [ref=e895]:\n              - img [ref=e896]\n              - text: 3.5k\n            - generic [ref=e900]: ★ 10\n            - generic [ref=e901]: 1 v\n        - 'link \"Neural Memory /neural-memory Associative memory with spreading activation for persistent, intelligent recall. Use PROACTIVELY when: (1) You need to remember facts, decisions, errors, or context across sessions (2) User asks \\\"do you remember...\\\" or references past conversations (3) Starting a new task — inject relevant context from memory (4) After making decisions or encountering errors — store for future reference (5) User asks \\\"why did X happen?\\\" — trace causal chains through memory Zero LLM dependency. Neural graph with Hebbian learning, memory decay, contradiction detection, and temporal reasoning. by @nhadaututtheky 3.1k ★ 2 1 v\" [ref=e902] [cursor=pointer]':\n          - /url: /nhadaututtheky/neural-memory\n          - generic [ref=e903]:\n            - generic [ref=e904]:\n              - generic [ref=e905]: Neural Memory\n              - generic [ref=e906]: /neural-memory\n            - generic [ref=e907]: \"Associative memory with spreading activation for persistent, intelligent recall. Use PROACTIVELY when: (1) You need to remember facts, decisions, errors, or context across sessions (2) User asks \\\"do you remember...\\\" or references past conversations (3) Starting a new task — inject relevant context from memory (4) After making decisions or encountering errors — store for future reference (5) User asks \\\"why did X happen?\\\" — trace causal chains through memory Zero LLM dependency. Neural graph with Hebbian learning, memory decay, contradiction detection, and temporal reasoning.\"\n            - generic [ref=e909]:\n              - generic [ref=e910]: by\n              - generic [ref=e912]: \"@nhadaututtheky\"\n          - generic [ref=e913]:\n            - generic [ref=e914]:\n              - img [ref=e915]\n              - text: 3.1k\n            - generic [ref=e919]: ★ 2\n            - generic [ref=e920]: 1 v\n        - link \"Memory /memory Infinite organized memory that complements your agent's built-in memory with unlimited categorized storage. by @ivangdavila 3k ★ 4 3 v\" [ref=e921] [cursor=pointer]:\n          - /url: /ivangdavila/memory\n          - generic [ref=e922]:\n            - generic [r